Vagina short and approximately one-third of penis length. Dart apparatus large, long cylindrical, and located on atrium at vagina and penis junction. Gametolytic organ (sac and duct) small and long cylindrical tube. Free oviduct cylindrical, approximately as long as vagina, and proximal end encircled with thick tissue (Fig. 
47A
).

Sarika dugasti

occurs in central, north and western Thailand along the Tenasserim Ranges (Fig. 
44
) and the Salween Valley, east of the Dawna Ranges in Myanmar (
Blanford and Godwin-Austen 1908
; 
Pholyotha et al. 2020c
). However, the literature records from Laos, Nepal and Vietnam (
Schileyko 2011
; Inkahvilay et al. 2019) are still uncertain.
